        <td>Is Houston the world’s most freeway-focused city—the ultimate freeway metropolis? There are many potential competitors for such a distinction, and typically Los Angeles is automatically awarded that title. But Houston’s freeways have a certain design feature that elevates the freeway to a higher level of importance in the functioning of the city than nearly all other cities. It’s a feature that exists extensively only in Texas, and its prevalence in Houston is unequalled by any other city.
The freeway design feature is, of course, the freeway frontage road.
								
        </td>
