        <td>A much larger challenge to frontage roads emerged at the Texas Transportation Commission in June 2001. The commission approved a resolution to drastically curtail the construction of frontage roads on future limited-access highways in Texas. A series of public meetings was held, and public comment was overwhelmingly negative towards the new policy. In May 2002 the Texas Transportation Commission withdrew the proposed new policies on frontage roads without discussion. The Texas frontage road would live, and Texas would remain unique in the world with its dedication to frontage roads.								
        </td>
