        <td>Scatteration. Dispersion. Urban sprawl. These were terms the public was beginning to hear from public officials starting in the mid-1950s. Urban planners in Houston definitely took note of the movement toward low-density development, but viewed low-density suburbanization as an unstoppable trend and the best strategy was to accommodate it—with freeways.								
